1
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:22,340
(Directed by Li Yuxi)

2
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:27,780
=My Marvellous Fable=

3
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:40,380
=Episode 13=

4
00:01:40,820 --> 00:01:43,660
(Wuhan)

5
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,180
(Although)

6
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:47,180
(I know that it sounded absurd,)

7
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,380
(it did happen.)

8
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:54,900
(The death anniversary
of Ms. Wang's father is approaching.)

9
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:57,820
(I don't know why.)

10
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:00,380
(But I'm more anxious than her.)

11
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:04,740
(We went all the way)

12
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:06,740
(to Zhanjiang in two days.)

13
00:02:08,020 --> 00:02:08,540
(I don't want to drive)

14
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,300
(Zhanjiang)
(on the highway ever again.)

15
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:15,980
Feng Tianlan.

16
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:17,580
Have you bought the ticket?

17
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:21,780
What ticket?

18
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,060
(I never thought that I would need)

19
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:29,740
(to buy a ferry ticket)

20
00:02:30,340 --> 00:02:32,620
(for the car to drive to Hainan.)

21
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:40,620
(Although I paid 600
for the ferry ticket myself,)

22
00:02:42,420 --> 00:02:43,300
(the good news is)

23
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:45,020
(that this time,)

24
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:46,620
(I got the receipt.)

25
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:08,460
(Qionghai)

26
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:21,500
Thank you.

27
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,700
Aren't you going to eat it?

28
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,620
I'm so envious of you.

29
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:29,900
You eat everything with so much gusto.

30
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:35,420
Don't you think that the food in Hainan

31
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:37,220
is way more delicious
than the salad before this?

32
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:44,860
Feng Tianlan.

33
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,060
What do you think about Hainan?

34
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,460
Hainan is quite a nice place.

35
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:52,140
The sea is beautiful.

36
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:53,220
It's very wide.

37
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,620
It feels very comfortable here.

38
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:03,020
This place is not like Beijing.

39
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:06,300
It doesn't have
any drastic seasonal changes.

40
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:09,780
So, it'll make you feel

41
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:11,220
that time passes by very slowly here.

42
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:14,900
The wider the ocean,

43
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:17,340
the smaller I feel.

44
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:19,420
As if I were just a tiny grain...

45
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:21,420
of sand.

46
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,060
Let's eat.

47
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,420
Since you are enjoying the food so much,

48
00:04:38,780 --> 00:04:39,300
let me tell you a fact

49
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,540
that will ruin your appetite.

50
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:41,340
Okay?

51
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,420
What can you say to ruin my appetite?

52
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:46,100
For example...

53
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,420
my dad is still alive.

54
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:15,660
Ms. Wang, what are you trying to do?

55
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,100
I'm telling you the truth.

56
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:20,100
The truth?

57
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:21,980
The truth is,
your father is still alive.

58
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:23,420
What are we doing here then?

59
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:25,900
Going home.

60
00:05:26,340 --> 00:05:27,220
Going home?

61
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,460
Why do you want to go home?

62
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:30,100
For no reason

63
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,340
other than I want to go back.

64
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,740
Think about it carefully.

65
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,740
You told me you were rushing back
for the funeral.

66
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,220
Funeral! Ms. Wang.

67
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:39,220
I know.

68
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,620
But isn't it great right now?

69
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,220
My dad is still alive.

70
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:43,340
And no more funerals.

71
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,420
I told you

72
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:46,540
not to joke about your parents

73
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:47,540
and any elders like this.

74
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:12,340
The car is running out of petrol.

75
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:13,340
I'll fill up the tank for you

76
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,300
at the next petrol station.

77
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:15,500
Then, I'll find you a designated driver

78
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:16,620
and we'll part ways.

79
00:06:31,420 --> 00:06:33,900
What should we do now?

80
00:06:44,060 --> 00:06:44,580
Hello?

81
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:55,460
(10 KM away from Wang Putao's Home)

82
00:06:55,460 --> 00:07:04,700
(20 KM away from Wang Putao's Home)

83
00:07:30,540 --> 00:07:31,860
What brought you here to me?

84
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,540
You scared me.

85
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:38,460
My car broke down.

86
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,340
What a coincidence.

87
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:41,420
It's a good thing.

88
00:07:42,780 --> 00:07:44,660
Just now, I went to spy on him.

89
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,340
He carried that huge suitcase
up to the room

90
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:47,740
all by himself.

91
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:48,460
He's so strong.

92
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:51,180
Much more reliable
than all the other useless men

93
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,100
before him.

94
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:53,860
What is it?

95
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:55,420
Do you like him?

96
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:56,740
What do you mean?

97
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:57,780
Of course I like him.

98
00:07:57,980 --> 00:07:59,540
I can tell that he's a good boy.

99
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:01,980
Stop it.

100
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,220
I know that you like him.

101
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,900
Before my sister passed away,

102
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:07,660
she entrusted you to me.

103
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,660
I literally raised you.

104
00:08:10,980 --> 00:08:12,100
I know

105
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,420
how you look and act

106
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:14,420
when you like someone.

107
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:20,540
How's my dad lately?

108
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:22,780
Can he recognize some of you, at least?

109
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:24,980
He's still the same.

110
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,300
But I'm quite happy

111
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,420
that you've come back.

112
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:29,540
What is it?

113
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,620
Are you ready to see him now?

114
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,740
Save me some food.

115
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:49,860
Hurry up.

116
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,860
We are not celebrating
any festival today.

117
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:05,340
You don't have to bow to me.

118
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:06,500
Well.

119
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,140
I'm going back to my room.

120
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:09,940
Wait.

121
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,820
We don't have anything
to cook for dinner.

122
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:13,500
Let's go to the market together.

123
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:15,340
Come on.

124
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:16,740
I'm coming along.

125
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:19,340
Putao.

126
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,220
Let's go.

127
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:20,820
Hurry up.

128
00:09:20,820 --> 00:09:21,940
Putao!

129
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:11,620
How much is this?

130
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:12,980
Ten.

131
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,060
So expensive!

132
00:10:14,340 --> 00:10:15,140
What about this one?

133
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:16,340
Two yuan for one.

134
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,820
Two yuan for one?

135
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:19,060
Yes. We are running a small business.

136
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,220
A small business?

137
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:20,980
Can I taste it?

138
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:23,700
One balloon, please.

139
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:39,740
Don't simply run around without a phone.

140
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,220
Who will look for you if you are lost?

141
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:01,100
♪I am spellbound♪

142
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:03,420
♪How should I introduce you?♪

143
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:05,540
♪What I feel for you♪

144
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:07,780
♪Is beyond our friendship♪

145
00:11:08,740 --> 00:11:10,500
♪When something happens♪

146
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:13,220
♪You are the first person♪

147
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:15,620
♪I want to share it with♪

148
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:20,100
♪What kind of magic is it♪

149
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,460
♪That can change
the rate of my heartbeat?♪

150
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,980
♪I want to see you♪

151
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:27,140
♪Not because of the reasons I uttered♪

152
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:29,860
♪You've lodged yourself in my heart♪

153
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:32,420
♪I can't help but think of you♪

154
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:35,380
♪I don't care about anything else♪

155
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:38,500
♪Because I've started♪

156
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,060
♪To miss you again♪

157
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:41,340
She's quite happy

158
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:42,460
when she's with you.

159
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,860
She's happy?

160
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:45,740
She

161
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:48,060
is just a liar
who never tells the truth.

162
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:49,340
♪From the moment I see you♪

163
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:51,140
She's going to make trouble again.

164
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:52,860
♪I want to keep you♪

165
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:54,300
♪For myself♪

166
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:56,580
♪Who can save me?♪

167
00:11:57,860 --> 00:12:03,300
♪I hope that time
can stand still at this moment♪

168
00:12:22,580 --> 00:12:23,460
This place is so messy.

169
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:24,620
Do people ever come here?

170
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:25,980
You came.

171
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,340
Do you know each other well?

172
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:30,340
My older sister is her mother.

173
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,340
I am her aunt.

174
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:32,260
Come on, call me Aunt.

175
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:33,220
Dream on.

176
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:34,220
You are just a few years older than me.

177
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:34,980
I'm still older than you anyway.

178
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,140
Wait!

179
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:37,460
What is that?

180
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,220
Fried pork lard.
Have you not seen it before?

181
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:41,340
Feng, where are you from?

182
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:41,980
I'm from Shandong.

183
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:44,100
You are from the north?

184
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:44,700
No!

185
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,980
Don't add water to it!

186
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:47,220
Ms. Wang,

187
00:12:47,220 --> 00:12:48,500
can you step away?

188
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,620
Don't make things harder for us.

189
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:50,900
Go away and entertain yourself.

190
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:53,100
Feng.

191
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:53,820
You are from Shandong.

192
00:12:53,820 --> 00:12:54,940
What does your family do?

193
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,100
When I was young,

194
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:57,100
my family made clothes.

195
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:59,060
After we made some money,

196
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:00,220
we had many relatives

197
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,580
who loved hanging out together.

198
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:03,260
So, besides clothes,

199
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,940
we dabbled in auto parts,

200
00:13:04,940 --> 00:13:05,620
pump valves,

201
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:06,460
et cetera.

202
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:09,220
So you are the young master
of a business family.

203
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:12,460
I'm just a helper at most.

204
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:14,220
Are you investigating
his family background?

205
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:16,060
I'm doing it for your own good.

206
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:18,380
Feng, you have a great personality.

207
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:19,260
Am I right?

208
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:20,820
- He's just faking it.
- I'm just putting up with her.

209
00:13:48,260 --> 00:13:48,980
Ms. Wang.

210
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:52,700
If there's nothing else,

211
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:54,100
I'll go back to rest now.

212
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:58,940
Feng Tianlan.

213
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:08,340
I'm sorry.

214
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:16,620
After some serious thought,

215
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:18,820
I realized that I had gone too far

216
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:20,060
with my lie.

217
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,860
But I didn't mean to do that.

218
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:38,460
Here are some osmanthus wine

219
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:39,700
and side dishes.

220
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:40,780
Continue with your conversation.

221
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:16,740
Feng Tianlan.

222
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:17,740
I realize that you...

223
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:21,220
are so ridiculous.

224
00:15:42,620 --> 00:15:43,260
I never thought

225
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,140
that you

226
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:46,740
would serve me once, Ms. Wang.

227
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:49,380
But the wine is so delicious.

228
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:50,980
Why aren't you drinking it?

229
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:54,340
Because I don't want
to make someone worry about me.

230
00:15:58,940 --> 00:15:59,740
Ms. Wang.

231
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,980
Today, you look a little bit...

232
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:05,580
You are really relying

233
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,300
on liquid courage.

234
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:16,980
To be honest, Wang Putao,

235
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:18,860
sometimes,

236
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:19,980
I really don't know

237
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,740
what you are thinking about.

238
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:22,460
And I don't know

239
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:24,140
how many secrets you are hiding.

240
00:16:25,260 --> 00:16:27,380
But I have to remind myself every day

241
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,740
to find out what you are thinking.

242
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:32,620
I'm exhausted.

243
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,460
You are already talking nonsense

244
00:16:37,140 --> 00:16:38,940
after drinking
just a little bit of wine.

245
00:16:39,620 --> 00:16:41,460
I used to hold my liquor very well.

246
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,820
Actually, I'm really envious of you.

247
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:54,860
Envious of me?

248
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,460
Why?

249
00:17:02,340 --> 00:17:03,100
Do you know

250
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,740
why you can't talk nonsense

251
00:17:04,740 --> 00:17:05,500
about an elder's death?

252
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:18,300
"The sun sets slowly down the hills;

253
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,540
The Yellow River flows into the ocean.

254
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,420
Should you see
a thousand miles further,

255
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:24,260
Ascend to a higher level."

256
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:26,340
You are so good with the poem.

257
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:27,940
Can you recite other poems?

258
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:28,820
I'm sleepy.

259
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:29,140
You are sleepy?

260
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:30,300
Come. Lie down.

261
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,900
Let me turn off the fan for you.

262
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:36,020
No. It's too hot.

263
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:37,340
Too hot?

264
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:38,620
I don't want you to catch a cold.

265
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:39,300
I'd better turn it off.

266
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:40,300
I'll be fine. Don't turn it off.

267
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,180
Okay. We'll keep it on.

268
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:43,620
Sleep.

269
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:54,340
(When I was young,)

270
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:56,820
(I thought that we had a lot of time.)

271
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,340
(I thought that my grandma
would always be with me.)

272
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,580
But that was the last time

273
00:18:07,860 --> 00:18:09,020
I saw her.

274
00:18:14,420 --> 00:18:15,700
(She had a fever the next day.)

275
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,340
Our family thought that she was fine.

276
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:20,900
And that it was just a normal cold.

277
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:22,780
I thought so too.

278
00:18:24,860 --> 00:18:26,500
So, I went to school.

279
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:31,100
(But in just a few days,)

280
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:34,620
(my grandma...)

281
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:39,020
(was diagnosed with pneumonia.)

282
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:43,380
(After that...)

283
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:49,060
(From that moment onward,)

284
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:51,020
(I felt so guilty about it.)

285
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:53,100
(Of course,)

286
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:56,100
I felt guilty
about Zhang Haibei's death too.

287
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:01,860
(So)

288
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:03,500
(when you told me
that you wanted to go home)

289
00:19:03,780 --> 00:19:05,100
(to pay respects to your dad,)

290
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:06,500
